{
  "stem": "2946.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we had a wooden stick about the size of about a quarter of a meter.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And with the handle-- with the-- a-- a rubber handle, a rubber-- rubber- a piece of rubber holding to our hands.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was our only weapon we had.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, duty-- the duties were-- there were six or-- six at least six of these barracks where the army was originally, army was housed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lot of these barracks had maybe holding eight, seven hundred soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So what we did was evacuate-- taken away-- and this was made a ubication for the Jews who came from Slovakia, Czechoslovakia, from Germany, from Holland, from-- from all-- all kind of small countries, over Europe, really was-- except Poland.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Hungary-- Hungarian Jews came, Slovakian Jew, I told you that, Czechoslovakian Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, we were-- we were stationed in these barracks at the gate, and everybody had to have a reason to walk through, and we checked these people, whether they have the right to be-- if they live there-- so we let them in.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were kitchens where these people-- the Jews-- there were maybe in one barrack 800 people, or thousands of people, maybe, housed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because at one time, Theresienstadt had about 40,000, maybe even 60,000, Jews there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And gradually, almost every second, there were transfers going, trains taking them to the east.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Although we didn't know what east meant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So the kitchens were there, and they were feeding people lined up here with a piece of dish, and the cooks were putting the food in, but not much to-- to food.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the-- the cooks were stealing the food, taking it home to their families or themselves, and we checked them at the door.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
